race.comment: The well-related PEREILLE (3) (full to G2 winner Corniche) looked good saluting in the first run for the new stable before being tipped out for a spell. Has tuned up for this with two recent trials and has a solid fresh record with two wins and three placings from seven first-up attempts. Looks very hard to toss. SURPRISE HONEY (13) has troubled the judge in all six outings this campaign and it's hard to knock mares in form. Cannot be discounted. STREET CHASE (11) won well in the small field two back before turning in a poor one last time out when well beaten. Happy to overlook that poor effort and expect him to bounce back today. CASPERNOVA (2) won well here last time out as a $2.60 chance and drops in weight today. Will love the sting out of the ground and can play a leading role.
